OL,3,CAnguish and outrage: Remembering the
OL,4,Cdrowned valley of Tryweryn 60 years on
OL,6,FIt's one of the most sobering and
OL,7,Femotive sites in all of Wales. Llyn
OL,8,FCelyn reservoir, near Bala in Gwynedd,
OL,9,Fwas officially opened in October 1965
OL,10,Fto provide water for the city of
OL,11,FLiverpool.
OL,13,FThe huge artificial lake had been 10
OL,14,Fyears in the planning and was to prove
OL,15,Fhugely controversial. It led to the
OL,16,Fdemolition of a centuries-old village
OL,17,Fand the comprehensive flooding of a
OL,18,Fvast valley. An entire way of life was
OL,19,Fswept away.
