OL,3,CAnguish and outrage: Remembering the
OL,4,Cdrowned valley of Tryweryn 60 years on
OL,6,FBeneath the still waters of Llyn Celyn
OL,7,Flie the ruins of the Welsh-speaking
OL,8,Fcommunity that was sacrificed for a
OL,9,Fcity's demand for water. The village
OL,10,Fof Capel Celyn had a school, a chapel
OL,11,Fand even a post office. On the
OL,12,Fsurrounding hills of the Tryweryn
OL,13,FValley were cottages and farms, where
OL,14,Ffamilies had worked the land for
OL,15,Fgeneration after generation.
