OL,3,CAnguish and outrage: Remembering the
OL,4,Cdrowned valley of Tryweryn 60 years on
OL,6,FBuddug Medi used to preach at the
OL,7,Fchapel, remembering: "It meant
OL,8,Feverything to the people of Capel
OL,9,FCelyn. It was well attended and was
OL,10,Fthe centre of our lives. I first
OL,11,Fpreached there when I was 19 and the
OL,12,Fbuilding was actually used for lots of
OL,13,Fthings, as well as religion. We used
OL,14,Fto hold eisteddfodau there. But when
OL,15,Fthe chapel was demolished it was the
OL,16,Fend of social life and religious life,
OL,17,Fboth together. It was heartbreaking.
OL,18,FAll that remained was dust. All that
OL,19,Fhistory was lost."
