OL,3,CAnguish and outrage: Remembering the
OL,4,Cdrowned valley of Tryweryn 60 years on
OL,6,FAeron Prysor Jones was born and bred
OL,7,Fin the village. He said: "A firm of
OL,8,Fcontractors arrived in the valley and
OL,9,Fthey started digging holes in
OL,10,Fpractically every field. Of course
OL,11,Fthey were questioned as to what was
OL,12,Fgoing on and the answer was given that
OL,13,Fthey were making a survey to see what
OL,14,Fthe mineral content of the valley was.
OL,15,FAnd people took them at their word.
OL,17,F"But as time went on it was obvious
OL,18,Fthat the point of these holes was just
OL,19,Fto find out whether they had enough
OL,20,Fresources within the valley to build
OL,21,Fthe dam from within the valley.
