OL,3,CAnguish and outrage: Remembering the
OL,4,Cdrowned valley of Tryweryn 60 years on
OL,6,FOne of the children displaced by the
OL,7,Fdemolition of Capel Celyn was a young
OL,8,Fboy with a very special name: Tryweryn
OL,9,FEvans. He still remembers the final
OL,10,Fdays of his village.
OL,12,F"When everything had been knocked
OL,13,Fdown, as children we were thinking,
OL,14,F'why have they done this? What's going
OL,15,Fto happen to us? We've got to live a
OL,16,Fnew life in a new place'," he said.
OL,18,F"For years afterwards I used to think,
OL,19,F'are we ever going back there?' It
OL,20,Fmight have just been a bad dream. It
OL,21,Fwas so sad."
